The paper proposes a deep learning method for unsupervised domain adaptation, which involves leveraging a labeled source domain to learn a classifier for an unlabeled target domain with a different distribution. This falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and specifically involves computer vision (cs.CV) as the target domain is likely to involve image data. The method also involves clustering and alignment, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), and neural networks (cs.NE).
